Dear Honorable Governor Perdue

            I appreciate the difficult task you face with the North Carolina budget this year but I want to bring a serious public safety issue to your attention that has gone unaddressed too long.  There are over 400 fire departments in North Carolina that protect NC State owned properties.  These properties range from the General Assembly building to the campus of UNC to a Highway Patrol station in the mountains.  There is a fund called the State Fire Protection fund that totals about $5,453,000 that is set aside each year to reimburse those fire departments for the cost of the services rendered.  The problem for years now has been that the fund is over ½ what it should be for equitable reimbursement.  I have attached information to help demonstrate that need.  The budget office of the previous administration twice promised to correct this inequity that places an unfair burden on the taxpayers of the jurisdiction where particular State facilities are placed and they twice failed to do so.



Rep. Verla Insko has (once again) introduced legislation to correct this inequity (H-355) and increase the fund which would address this public safety need.  The people of North Carolina have a significant investment in the facilities of this State and the need to provide adequate fire protection to protect that investment becomes even more acute during financially tight times.  If you cant afford to protect it, will you be able to afford to replace it?  Local fire departments are financially strapped in these times as well and the State should have an obligation to pay fair share for adequate fire protection.  For 187 of these fire departments, it is not an insignificant portion of their annual budgets (see distribution lists attached).  These dollars are also important to the economy of our State as well because local fire departments put the dollars back into the states economic flow through salaries paid, supplies purchased, diesel fuel purchased, equipment repaired and purchased and utilities paid.



Governor, I ask that you support the amendment to add dollars to the State Fire Fund and address the public safety needs of fire departments protecting the lives of NC State employees and NC owned facilities.  In the scope of the State budget this is not large dollars but these are critical dollars that have been missing for way too long and the economic crunch on local fire departments has made it much worse.  I and many other Fire Chiefs across our state are willing to work with your budget staff to help address this problem.  Please let us know how you can assist us or we can assist you with this issue.



